<subSubSection id="F9C2864D2EDA52C114D6811C2025A4BB" type="description">
<paragraph id="49077825EDC13370F70812F17DABB084" pageNumber="128">
[[worker]]. - Couleur plus claire que 
<taxonomicName id="C54FEAA6DC08E8B5EE861BA35C0F6335" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33034" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Oecophylla" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oecophylla longinoda (Latreille)" lsidName-HNS="Oecophylla longinoda (Latreille)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longinoda">longinoda Latr.</taxonomicName>
de l'Afrique occidentale, comme 
<taxonomicName id="6CADBBB9499B093C9617966231CFFD9D" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33040" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Oecophylla" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oecophylla smaragdina (Fabricius)" lsidName-HNS="Oecophylla smaragdina (Fabricius)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smaragdina">smaragdina</taxonomicName>
in sp.; taille aussi grande que chez celle-ci, mais le n oe ud du pedicule est beaucoup plus court, plus court meme que chez la 
<taxonomicName id="480E76E8AC6CE1559073825B12C7FB9D" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33034" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Oecophylla" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oecophylla longinoda (Latreille)" lsidName-HNS="Oecophylla longinoda (Latreille)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longinoda">longinoda</taxonomicName>
typique. La tete est un peu plus large et la dent apicale des mandibules un peu plus courte.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D8FBB69A76A243548FDE5EB2785676B3" pageNumber="128">
[[queen]]. - Couleur verdatre de 
<taxonomicName id="2B153067511645B02C78D1AF833C128B" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33040" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Oecophylla" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oecophylla smaragdina (Fabricius)" lsidName-HNS="Oecophylla smaragdina (Fabricius)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smaragdina">smaragdina</taxonomicName>
in sp., mais le n oe ud plus etroit avec un sillon median moins profond. Faisant passage a 
<taxonomicName id="7E6AB85C27DCF34A19D1B15BBE176E44" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33034" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Oecophylla" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oecophylla longinoda (Latreille)" lsidName-HNS="Oecophylla longinoda (Latreille)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longinoda">longinoda Latr.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6793E030B5E9E2EA38D9B297AD6CAF69" pageNumber="128">
La 
<taxonomicName id="82B6177A7CC7EAF2432543A1BA49FB9C" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:228210" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Oecophylla" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oecophylla smaragdina var. brevinodis" lsidName-HNS="Oecophylla smaragdina var. brevinodis" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="smaragdina" variety="brevinodis">var. brevinodis Andre</taxonomicName>
est beaucoup plus petite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
